Police Minister Bheki Cele spoke to eNCA's Thulasizwe Simelane and Tumelo Mothotoane on several issues in the police force. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Police Minister Bheki Cele admits that there are rotten apples in the South African Police Service. Cele was in conversation with eNCA on Tuesday. Police in the country have faced one of their biggest challenges since implementing lockdown regulations. READ: Policing facing new challenges, says Cele Over the past few months, a number of police brutality cases have been reported. This has impacted on the relationship between authorities and communities. Watch the full interview in the video gallery above